-- EDF Halts Blayais-2 Nuclear Plant; Current French Halts
-- B y   R a c h e l   M o r i s o n
-- 2012-08-01T11:05:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/edf-halts-blayais-2-nuclear-plant-current-french-halts-table-.html
Electricite de France SA halted its
910-megawatt Blayais-2 nuclear power plant today, according to
the nation’s grid operator, Reseau de Transport d’Electricite.  EDF delayed the start of its 1,330-megawatt Paluel-3 unit
by two days to Aug. 7 following maintenance, RTE data show.  EDF, the world’s biggest nuclear power plant operator, has
40 reactors online, representing 68 percent of available nuclear
capacity, RTE data show. EDF’s 58 atomic plants generate about
78 percent of the country’s power.  The following table lists EDF’s nuclear units that are out
of  service , their generating capacity in megawatts, when they
stopped and the expected return date, if known, according to
RTE. Two asterisks highlight an unplanned halt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Morison in London at 
